.TH "rza1_gpio_request" 9 "rza1_gpio_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rza1_gpio_request \- configure pin in port mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rza1_gpio_request
.BI "(struct gpio_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "unsigned int gpio "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
gpio chip where the gpio sits on
.IP "gpio" 12
gpio offset
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Configure a pin as gpio (port mode).
After reset, the pin is in input mode with input buffer disabled.
To use the pin as input or output, set_direction shall be called first
